Object-Oriented Programming is a class of programming that includes languages that implement Objects. An Object, in most basic terms, is a living instance of a Class. Therefore, a programminglanguage that allows the programmer to define and implement Classes is Object-Oriented.

Some of the most common components an Object-Oriented Programming Language may possess are:

Abstraction
Polymorphism
Inheritance
Encapsulation
These allow you to perform certain tasks and implement features that non-OOP languages do not offer